@node Beat "The Beat« goes on..."
If you haven't spent the last few months on Mars, you should know that the
Swiss watchmaker Swatch« has made the 2nd attempt to re-define
the unit of time (the 1st attempt was during the French revolution)
with the Beat«, a timezone-less unit that defines the length of a day
as 1000 Beats«.

So 12 p.m. in Switzerland is @500, but also @500 in Tokyo
and @500 in New York etc... 

@{b}IMPORTANT@{ub} the @{"TZ" link TZ} ENV-variable has to be set to
the right value!

@endnode
@node TZ "The timezones"

The ENV:TZ variable must start with your timezone as 3 letter code
+ @{b}negative@{ub} offset from GMT in a 
@{b}POSIX compliant format@{ub} @{u}<- Changed!@{uu}

Valid formats are:
GMT+0 (Speaks for itself)

CET-1
MET-1 (Western and Central Europe)
CDT-2 ( "" Daylight saving time)

PDT+8 (If you're Steve Ballmer ;)
@endnode
@node Usage "If you order now, all extra options are absolutely free of charge!"

You can still run this version like the old one, (without arguments)
but the real fun starts with the new options :-)

Well Jim, if I type @{b}Beet ONCE@{ub}, what cool exiting thing will happen?
Mike, that's a really neat option for simple scripts and the like.
It prints out the .beat time once and exits without any tricks and hassle
within just milliseconds!

I'm pretty amazed Jim, but @{b}Beet WAIT@{ub} has two options of it's own:
@{b}Beet WAIT 5@{ub} will wait until the .beat time is devideble by 5 and
@{b}Beet WAIT @123@{ub} is a .beat equivalent to @{u}Wait UNTIL=12:23@{uu}!!!

Mike, you forgot to metion @{b}Beet ENV@{ub}, the new and powerful option that
creates and updates the ENV-variable @{u}BEAT@{uu}! Just as a special
request by one of our many happy costumers!!!

And don't forget, Jim, this one-time offer can be stopped at any time,
simply by pressing Ctrl-C, isn't that great!!!






              @{i}Commercial Presentation@{ui}
@endnode
@node History "Long time ago, on an A1200/060 far away..."

Damn, more than a year went by since te previous release...
What the !@#$%^&* happened during that time???

Ę I forgot all about it

Ę It just sat there on my HD

Ę I made a small internal update (never to be released);
 Ę Now accepts TZ variable in POSIX-compliant format (as it @{b}SHOULD@{ub} be)
   (my stupid mistake, only TIMEZONE (and yam_TZ for that matter) should
    contain an RFC compliant timzone setting)
 Ę Calculation error fixed(!!)
 Ę Beet ONCE option added

Ę Beet WAIT sees the daylight...

Ę I finally got my diploma and spent the next 4 months being a lame excuse
  for a lazy unemployed slob :-/

Ę My HD crashed (1.3G) :((

Ę Stripped my savings account for a new one (13.5G) :]

Ę I blew my HD controller :-((((((((((((((((((((((((((

Ę An ad-hoc admission halfway-a-semester turns my life upside-down...
  Back to student life and now on my way to a science degree (I hope)

Ę Went to Cologne with yoda, Mr. Oizo and a whole busload of Amigans
  (Yess...) and got myself a PowerFlyer IDE controller

Ę A1200/060 back online....

Ę Recovered my old sources

Ę Added Beet ENV

Ę Code's really messy now

Ę >>Code cleanup!!<<

Ę This release!!!

@endnode
